Define sum and mean functions to handle NAs appropriately

#Define function to correctly sum across duplicates (sum(NA,NA,NA) = NA, while sum(1,NA,NA) = 1, which is not the default for na.rm parameter)

my_sum <- function(x){
  if(all(is.na(x))){
    return(NA)
  }
  else{
    return(sum(x, na.rm = TRUE))
  }
}

#Define function to correctly sum across duplicates (sum(NA,NA,NA) = NA, while sum(1,NA,NA) = 1, which is not the default for na.rm parameter)

my_mean <- function(x){
  if(all(is.na(x))){
    return(NA)
  }
  else{
    return(mean(x, na.rm = TRUE))
  }
}

Regional characteristics


#make depth numeric
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,depth := as.numeric(depth)]

#make survey and survey unit factors
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,survey:=factor(survey)][,survey_unit:=factor(survey_unit)]

#adjust years
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,year_adj := year-min(year)+1]

#add column for yearly summed # of hauls
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,haul_id_count_annual := uniqueN(haul_id),.(year, survey_unit)]

#add column for yearly summed # of spp
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,spp_count_annual := uniqueN(accepted_name),.(year, survey_unit)]

#add column for avg depth per year
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,depth_annual_avg := my_mean(depth),.(year, survey_unit)]

#add column for avg latitude per year
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,latitude_annual_avg := my_mean(latitude),.(year, survey_unit)]

#add column for latitude range per year
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,latitude_annual_range := max(latitude, na.rm =T)-min(latitude, na.rm =T),.(year, survey_unit)]

#add column for depth range per year
FishGlob_clean.singleseason[,depth_annual_range := max(depth, na.rm =T)-min(depth, na.rm =T),.(year, survey_unit)]

Calculate coefficients from lm for trend in species richness within a region over time

#plot year vs richness for each reg
ggplot(data = FishGlob_richness_year_survey) +
  geom_point(aes(x = year, y = spp_count_annual), size = 2) +
  facet_wrap(~survey_unit, scales = "free") +
  theme_classic()


#simple lm
richness_trend_lm <- lm(spp_count_annual ~ year*survey_unit, data = FishGlob_richness_year_survey)

#Use linear algebra to calculate coefficients and standard errors
spp_richness_coefs.r <- data.table(lm_interaction_coefficients_se(richness_trend_lm))

#Add survey names
spp_richness_coefs.r[,survey_unit := sort(unique(jaccard_index_allyears$survey_unit))]
  
  colnames(spp_richness_coefs.r) <- c("term","survey_unit_richness_coefficient","richness_coefficient_error","t-value","p-value","survey_unit")
  
  spp_richness_coefs.r <- spp_richness_coefs.r[,.(survey_unit, survey_unit_richness_coefficient, richness_coefficient_error)]

#export this table
fwrite(spp_richness_coefs.r, file = here::here("output","spp_richness_coefs.r.csv"))

#survey_unit
region_stats <- as.data.table(matrix(nrow = length(all_survey_units)))

region_stats[,survey_unit := as.character(V1)][, survey := as.character(V1)][, spp_num := as.numeric(V1)][,mean_haul_id_count_annual := as.numeric()][,mean_haul_density := as.numeric()][,SD_haul_density := as.numeric()][, study_period := as.numeric(V1)][,first_year:= as.numeric()][,last_year := as.numeric()][, years_sampled := as.numeric(V1)][, lat_range := as.numeric(V1)][, mean_annual_cpue := as.numeric(V1)][, mid_lat := as.numeric(V1)][, lon_range := as.numeric(V1)][, area_km := as.numeric(V1)][, depth_range := as.numeric(V1)][,  mid_depth := as.numeric(V1)][, mean_temp := as.numeric(V1)][, mean_landings := as.numeric(V1)][,jaccard_coef := as.numeric()][,jaccard_coef_upr := as.numeric()][,jaccard_coef_lwr := as.numeric()][,Trend_jaccard := as.character()][,jaccard_abun_coef := as.numeric()][,jaccard_abun_coef_upr := as.numeric()][,jaccard_abun_coef_lwr := as.numeric()][,Trend_jaccard_abun := as.character()]

  region_stats[,V1:=NULL]

for (i in 1:length(all_survey_units)) {
  reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year <- FishGlob_clean.singleseason[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i]]

    
    #fix those that cross dateline
    reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,long_range := max(longitude)-min(longitude)]
    reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,long_shift := ifelse(long_range >300 & longitude > 0, longitude - 360, longitude)]
    
        ####unique lat lon
    lat_lon <- unique(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,.(latitude, long_shift)])
    
    pts <- st_as_sf(lat_lon, coords=c('long_shift','latitude'), crs=4326 )
    
    conc <- concaveman(pts, 1,2)
    
    #delete areas that overlap
    conc_nooverlap <- ms_erase(conc,world[1])
    
    sf_use_s2(FALSE) #helps with spherical geometry
    area <- st_area(conc_nooverlap) #m2

    #compile into region_Stats table    
                  region_stats[i,"survey_unit"] <- paste0(all_survey_units[i])
                  region_stats[i,"survey"] <- word(all_survey_units[i],1, sep = "_")
                  region_stats[i,"spp_num"] <- length(unique(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,accepted_name]))
                  region_stats[i,"mean_haul_id_count_annual"] <- my_mean(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,haul_id_count_annual])
                  region_stats[i,"mean_haul_density"] <- my_mean(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,haul_id_count_annual]/
                                                                   (area/(1000^2))) #per km^2
                  region_stats[i,"SD_haul_density"] <- sd(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[,haul_id_count_annual]/
                                                                   (area/(1000^2)))
                  region_stats[i,"first_year"] <- min(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year)
                  region_stats[i,"last_year"] <- max(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year)
                  region_stats[i,"study_period"] <- max(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year)-min(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year)+1
                  region_stats[i,"years_sampled"] <- length(unique(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year))
                  region_stats[i,"lat_range"] <- max(lat_lon$latitude)-min(lat_lon$latitude)
                  region_stats[i,"mid_lat"] <- my_mean(lat_lon$latitude)
                  region_stats[i, "mean_annual_cpue"] <- my_mean(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$num_cpue_annual)
                  region_stats[i,"lon_range"] <- max(lat_lon$long_shift)-min(lat_lon$long_shift)
                  region_stats[i,"area_km"] <- area/(1000^2)
                  region_stats[i,"depth_range"] <- max(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$depth, na.rm = T)-min(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$depth, na.rm = T)
                  region_stats[i,"mid_depth"] <- my_mean(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$depth)
                  region_stats[i,"mean_temp"] <- year_survey_unit_characteristics[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],mean_reg_temp_allyears]
                  region_stats[i,"mean_landings"] <- year_survey_unit_characteristics[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],mean_reg_fishing_allyears]
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_coef"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],estimate]
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_coef_lwr"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],lwr]
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_coef_upr"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],upr]
                  region_stats[i,"Trend_jaccard"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],`Significant Trends`]
                  
                  if(all_survey_units[i] %in% abun_subset){
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard_abundance[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],estimate]
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef_lwr"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard_abundance[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],lwr]
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef_upr"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard_abundance[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],upr]
                  region_stats[i,"Trend_jaccard_abun"] <- trend_coefs_jaccard_abundance[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i],`Significant Trends`]
                  }else{
                    region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef"] <- NA
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef_lwr"] <- NA
                  region_stats[i,"jaccard_abun_coef_upr"] <- NA
                  region_stats[i,"Trend_jaccard_abun"] <- NA
                    
                  }
                  
}

Calculate annual area of sampling (This takes a while)


#set up empty data table with year and region
region_area_byyear <- data.table(survey_unit = as.character(),year = as.numeric(), area_km = as.numeric())


for (i in 1:length(all_survey_units)) {
  reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year <- FishGlob_clean.singleseason[survey_unit == all_survey_units[i]]
  
  #then, year
  survey_years <- unique(reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year$year)
  
  #data table to fill
  
      #single table
    region_area_byyear_single <- as.data.table(matrix(nrow = length(survey_years)))
    region_area_byyear_single[,survey_unit := all_survey_units[i]][,year := as.integer(V1)][,area_km := as.numeric(V1)][,V1 := NULL]
    
    
  for (j in 1:length(survey_years)) {
    #single year
    FishGlob_1year <- reduced_FishGlob_clean.singleseasoned.10year[year == survey_years[j],]
    
        #fix those that cross dateline
    FishGlob_1year[,long_range := max(longitude)-min(longitude)]
    FishGlob_1year[,long_shift := ifelse(long_range >300 & longitude > 0, longitude - 360, longitude)]
    
        ####unique lat lon
    lat_lon <- unique(FishGlob_1year[,.(latitude, long_shift)])
    
    pts <- st_as_sf(lat_lon, coords=c('long_shift','latitude'), crs=4326 )
    
    conc <- concaveman(pts, 1,2)
    
    #delete areas that overlap with land
    conc_nooverlap <- ms_erase(conc,world[1])
    
    sf_use_s2(FALSE) #helps with spherical geometry
    area <- st_area(conc_nooverlap) #m2
    
    #compile into region_Stats table    
                  region_area_byyear_single[j,"year"] <- as.numeric(survey_years[j])
                  region_area_byyear_single[j,"area_km"] <- as.numeric(area/(1000^2))

                  paste0(all_survey_units[i],", ", "year ", j, " out of ",length(survey_years))
  }
  #merge across surveys
  region_area_byyear <- rbind(region_area_byyear, region_area_byyear_single)
                  }

Proportion test (prop homogenizing/differentiating vs.Â prop not)

H0: The null hypothesis is that the two hemispheres from which the regions were drawn have the same true proportion of homogenizers. A: The alternative is that this proportion is different in at least one of the hemispheres.

H0: The null hypothesis is that the two hemispheres from which the regions were drawn have the same true proportion of differentiators. A: The alternative is that this proportion is different in at least one of the hemispheres.

For Jaccard: Differentiation was more common in the southern hemisphere (four out of eight surveys), while homogenization was more common in the northern hemisphere (eight out of 29 surveys). START HERE


#JACCARD

                #N, S
homogenizers <- c(10,0)
differentiators <- c(9,3)
total_surveys <- c(25,9)


prop.test(homogenizers,total_surveys) #p value = 0.06, so groups are not different
